<div class="publication">
    <div class="publication-title">
        <h1>Mark van Loosdrecht</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="publication-editor" itemscope="" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
            <img src="https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/resources.elsevier-jci.com/resources/FCB4E89D-5056-8600-6C574AF5F0EC487D-jci_photo_export_8079.png" alt="Mark van Loosdrecht">
                    <span class="publication-editor-jobtitle" itemprop="jobTitle">Editor-in-Chief, Water Research</span>
                    <span class="publication-editor-affiliation" itemprop="affiliation">Department of Biochemical Engineering <br> Delft University of Technology <br> KWR Watercycle Research <br> Delft <br> Netherlands</span>
                    <div class="publication-editor-biography"><p>Professor in Environmental Biotechnology at the Delft University of Technology. Supervised around 50 PhD students and co-authored over 400 peer reviewed papers.Member of the royal academy of arts and sciences (KNAW) and of the academy of engineering (AcTI).editor in chief for Water Research</p></div>
                    <span class="publication-editor-send">Send an email to Mark van Loosdrecht</span>
            <p>
                To send an email to Mark van Loosdrecht please complete the short form below. Please note that all enquiries should relate specifically to Water Research.
                All the fields are required so please make sure you complete them all otherwise we won't be able to send your message.
            </p>
